com.siperian.sif.message.mrm

Class GetSearchResultsRequest

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.siperian.sif.message.SiperianRequest
      • com.siperian.sif.message.mrm.GetSearchResultsRequest
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable

    public class GetSearchResultsRequest
extends SiperianRequest
    Retrieves additional data when the number of records found by the SIF API search queries (SearchMatch, SearchQuery, GetMatchedRecords) exceeds the number of records to return specified in the search API request.

    The details of the paging support are explained in the SearchRequestBase class.

    Siperian Hub does not enforce the navigation direction and the data page size. The GetSearchResults allows retrieving any part of the resultset of a previously run search query.

    Required Parameters:

    All three parameters of this API setSearchToken(String), setRecordsToReturn(int), and setFirstRecord(int) are required.

    The following example requests the second page of data from a search displaying 10 records at a time.

    Usage Example:

    ...
    SearchQueryResponse sqResponse = (SearchQueryResponse)
    sipClient.process(request);
    String searchToken = sqResponse.getSearchToken();

    GetSearchResultsRequest request = new GetSearchResultsRequest();
    request.setSearchToken(searchToken);
    request.setRecordsToReturn(10);
    request.setFirstRecord(11);
    GetSearchResultsResponse response = (GetSearchResultsResponse) sipClient.process(request);
    See Also:
    GetSearchResultsResponse, SearchMatchRequest, SearchQueryRequest, SearchRequestBase, SearchResponseBase, GetMatchedRecordsRequest, Serialized Form

    API Pair: GetSearchResultsResponse

    API Group: Data Retrieval

      • setFirstRecord

        public void setFirstRecord(int firstRecord)
        Index of first record to return, starting with 1. The API will return an error if this parameter is set to a negative value or 0. The API will return no records if the first record parameter is set to a value greater than the number of records returned by the original search query.

        Parameters:
        firstRecord - Index of first record to return, starting with 1.

        public void setRecordsToReturn(int recordsToReturn)

        Parameters:
